nit: please write this as the longer 
```suggestion
  Equiv.bijective { toFun := PEquiv.symm, infFun := PEquiv.symm, left_inv := symm_symm, right_inv := symm_symm }
```
as this is more robust to future refactors of field layouts

I assume you'd like me to fix this in the existing manifestastions of this lemma (which use this layout?)

Actually it may be better to use `bijective_iff_has_inverse` because that is equivalent and in some sense avoids this strange "create an Equiv just to say that it is bijective" construction. I would make that change everywhere. (Basically the core reason this is true is "symm_symm", "symm_symm (the other way round)", "thus, bijective" and so these are just different ways of spelling that.)

What do you think?
Using `bijective_iff_has_inverse` sounds good, that save you one repetition of the word `symm`

```suggestion
theorem symm_bijective : Function.Bijective (LieEquiv.symm : L R L  L R L) :=
```

```suggestion
  Function.bijective_iff_has_inverse.mpr _, symm_symm, symm_symm
```
and in a few other places
